name: 6x4 Bathing Gentlemen.
description:
Here we have this unique priceless print featuring two strapping young gentlemen enjoying a self cleaning session with each other over a fine glass of vintage 1956 Merlot. 

Hang this exquisite piece over a fireplace or perhaps frame it and have it stand proudly on your whiskey cabinet. 

"For decor that screams decadence indulge yourself with this staple cornerstone of the collection which represents all that is good in the world. If it's gold-plated luxury you seek, you'll be able to relate to this piece on a level which the average art lover will adore. Throw your head back and laugh overtop your wine glass my friend, for it truly is half full."  -Jenn Brabbins PhD (Hons) Arts and Heritage specialist.

All prints come hand signed with a personal message and original wax seal of authenticity (seriously). 

Other sizes available upon request to order (up to 20x30").

name: 6x4 He Could Be Anything
description:
What could he be thinking I hear you ask, who knows, we may never know all we know is that he most probably beats his wife and has a fetish for out of date produce. 

"If there was ever an occasion to nonchalantly throw your jacket over your shoulder and sneer down the lens of your own mind's eye; it's worth considering what you would look like not only from the side, but from the front as well. Here the artist has captured the very depths of his dark psyche; juxtaposing the defiant confidence he may show the world with a deeper, slightly blurrier representation of his own sexual deviancy." - Jenn Brabbins PhD (Hons) Arts and Heratige Specialist.

Picture will come signed with a personal message and golden wax seal of originality.

name: 6x4 Who Left These Cakes Out?
description:
Uh oh! Somebody left some cakes out and this cheeky devil has been caught red handed! 
This picture can be suitable as a greetings card for any occasion, Birthdays, christmas, weddings, funerals, bar mitzvah's or even circumcisions!

"Who Left These Cakes Out, I feel conveys a tragic sadness reminiscent of the miss-spent youth we can relate to as a society; through the juxtaposition of temptation and submission. One rubber glove lies shed and discarded in a dark and troublesome metaphor of a body disrobed and giving into the darker sides of pleasure. The pure white of the surfaces has become tainted by the inherent need to gorge; and sate the appetite of the beast -a side we all conceal with our own rubber gloves of self preservation." - Jenn Brabbins PhD (Hons) Arts and Heritage specialist.

All prints come hand signed with a personal message and a gold wax seal of originality.

name: 6x4 Who's Doing The Dishes?
description:
Three contestants for the 2013 male model of the year got together for for a collaborative project expressing their love for doing the dishes and male nudity. 

Who's Doing The Dishes?

"This bold representation of a classic existential dilemma smacks of drama and colour; as the subjects take it in turns to explore the niche topic of kitchen eroticism. Particular detail has been taken to emphasise the simultaneously intimate act of interpersonal sponge-bathing with a shattered conscience behind the eyes of the forward facing males. 

We can only speculate as to the facial expression of the man in the sink; but his posture suggests a sort of divine ecstasy.The gentlemen indulge and frolic; but like the waters holding the iceberg that sunk the unsinkable Titanic; just what is it that lies behind the surface?" - Jenn Brabbins PhD (Hons) Arts and Heratige specialist. 

All prints come hand signed with a personal message and gold wax seal of originality. 

Other sizes available.
